- Design system with CSS custom properties
- Use RGB color values for theming
- When Supabase is configured: use Edge Functions for LLM and server-only logic; never expose API keys in the client

=== TASK ===
# Analytics & Reports

## Overview
Build a comprehensive Analytics & Reports system for Archject that delivers project- and account-level metrics (approval turnaround time, bottlenecked decisions, team response times), a Custom Report Builder with CSV export, alerting for SLA breaches, and admin-level monitoring/controls. This includes a user-facing Analytics & Reports page, Admin Tools & Analytics feature, and an Admin Dashboard page for enterprise user management, usage/health monitoring, and support ticket tracking. The implementation must follow the provided Visual Style and integrate with Archject’s decision and approval data model.

## Page Description (Full Detail)
This deliverable contains three tightly integrated surfaces:

1. Analytics & Reports (user-facing page)
   - What this page is: A workspace for project owners and team members to view analytics for a single project and account-level rollups. Primary goals are to surface approval turnaround time (median, mean, distribution), identify bottlenecked decisions (by reviewer, stage, or decision type), show team response times (time between comment and action), and allow exportable reports for legal/contract records.
   - Goals: Provide quick situational awareness, enable root-cause investigation of delays, and allow exporting of Decision Logs and custom metrics for offline archiving or legal use.
   - Connected features: Decision objects, project metadata, notifications/reminders subsystem, Reporting/Exports service, Admin Tools & Analytics for cross-account monitoring.
   - UI elements & visual guidance:
     - Top-level filters bar (date range selector, project selector, team/member selector, decision-type tags, SLA toggle)
     - KPI cards row: median approval time, % approved within SLA, total decisions in period, avg team response time
     - Bottleneck Heatmap card: matrix of decisions by status (Pending, In Review, Re-requested, Approved, Declined) vs time buckets (day/week) or by reviewer; hover shows counts and top decision examples
     - Decision Timeline / Distribution chart: histogram of approval times with selectable buckets; accent color (#0052CC) for primary series; muted gridlines
     - Table: Top slow decisions (sortable) showing decision ID, title, responsible reviewer, created date, time-to-decision, current status, link to decision
     - Custom Report Builder modal/panel: multi-select filters, aggregation choices (project/account), group-by (reviewer, decision type, status), predefined templates (Monthly SLA report, Decision Audit, Team Response), export CSV/JSON button
     - Alerts/Thresholds card: list of active alerts, ability to create new alert (e.g., median approval time > X hours for project), with toggle for email/push notifications and webhook integration
     - Export history: recent exported reports with metadata and download links
     - Visual design: Use card system, heavy whitespace, typography and colors per Visual Style section. Cards have subtle shadows, rounded corners, and hover elevation. Sidebar remains persistent for navigation.
   - API integrations: read-only integrations to Decision and Project APIs, Export API for CSV generation, Alerts API (create/manage), Admin APIs (for cross-account queries). Initially, project context states "No APIs connected" — treat that as "implement backend endpoints" to expose these analytics; implement aggregation jobs if necessary.

2. Admin Tools & Analytics (feature)
   - What this feature is: Admin interface and APIs to monitor platform usage, detect performance or health issues, manage enterprise accounts, and run cross-account analytics. Admin tools also include controls to manage enterprise roles, quotas, global alerts, and export/access audit logs.
   - Goals: Allow platform admins and enterprise account owners to see adoption, usage trends, reliability signals, and take administrative actions (deactivate account, reset user, escalate support).
   - UI elements: Admin analytics dashboard widgets, account list with usage metrics (decisions/month, active clients, exports), enterprise user management view (role assignment, SSO/SSO status), health checks (queue lag, background job failures), support tickets queue with SLA.
   - APIs: Admin endpoints for aggregated metrics, audit logs, support ticket management, and enterprise user management.

3. Admin Dashboard (page)
   - What this page is: A dedicated administrative area for platform-level monitoring and enterprise management.
   - Goals: Provide a single-pane-of-glass for admins to monitor system health, user management (enterprise customers), usage metrics, support tickets, and enforcement of compliance features.
   - UI elements: System health top-line indicators (API latency, DB errors, worker queue depth), account usage table with sorting and quick actions, support ticket list with status badges, an audit log search, and a global alerts manager.
   - Integration: This page reads from same aggregated metrics and audit logs produced by backend services and allows CRUD operations for enterprise accounts and admin-level alerts.

## Components to Build
- Frontend components:
  - AnalyticsFiltersBar: date-range picker, project/account selector, decision-type multi-select, SLA toggle, search
  - KPICardsRow: cards for median approval time, % within SLA, total decisions, avg response time
  - BottleneckHeatmap: interactive heatmap with hover tooltips and click-to-filter
  - DistributionHistogram: approval time histogram with brush/selection
  - SlowDecisionsTable: data table with server-side pagination, sorting, and links to decisions
  - ReportBuilderModal: filter builder, group-by, template selector, export button with progress state
  - AlertsManager: create/edit/delete alerts, threshold inputs, notification channel toggles
  - ExportHistoryList: recent exports, status, download link
  - AdminAnalyticsWidgets: usage charts, health indicators, account list rows
  - AdminUserManagement: list and detail views for users and roles, SSO status toggle, deactivate/reactivate
  - SupportTicketsList: ticket table with assign, comment, change status actions
  - Shared UI primitives: Card, Table, Modal, Tag / StatusPill, Badge, EmptyState, LoadingSkeleton

- Backend components:
  - Analytics API (project and account aggregations)
  - Report generation service (CSV/JSON exporter; queue + storage for large exports)
  - Alerts service (CRUD, evaluation engine to trigger notifications and webhooks)
  - Admin APIs (usage metrics, enterprise user management, audit logs, support tickets)
  - Aggregation workers / cron jobs for materialized metrics (daily/real-time where required)
  - Database schema extensions: analytics tables, alerts table, exports table, audit logs
  - Permissions & RBAC enforcement for admin vs project-level roles

## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend
- Build a responsive React (or chosen stack) page under /projects/:projectId/analytics and a global /admin/analytics route.
- Use the provided Visual Style tokens for colors, typography, spacing.
- Filters bar:
  - Date range picker (preset ranges: 7d, 30d, 90d, custom)
  - Project selector (dropdown with search)
  - Team/Member selector (multi-select)
  - Decision type/tag selector and status filter
  - SLA toggle that overlays SLA thresholds on KPI cards and chart
- KPI cards:
  - Display numeric values and small inline sparks (tiny line) showing trend (7d vs previous period)
  - Clicking a KPI applies filters and focuses chart/table
- BottleneckHeatmap:
  - Use canvas or SVG; x-axis = time buckets, y-axis = reviewers or status; color scale mapped to counts.
  - Hover tooltip shows breakdown and top 3 decisions; click drills to filtered table.
- Histogram/Distribution:
  - Interactive with bucket granularity slider; selecting bucket filters slow decision table.
- SlowDecisionsTable:
  - Columns: Checkbox, Decision ID (link), Title, Project, Reviewer, Created Date, Time to Decision, Status, Actions (View Decision, Create Task, Export)
  - Support server-side pagination, sorting, column resizing
- ReportBuilderModal:
  - Validations: require at least one project or account scope
  - Preview row count before export
  - On export, call Export API and show real-time export progress; show download link on completion
- AlertsManager:
  - Create alert form: name, scope (project/account), metric (median approval time, percent within SLA, pending count), threshold (value + operator), frequency, notification channels (email/webhook), enabled toggle.
  - Alerts list shows last triggered time and status
- Admin pages:
  - Admin Dashboard route (/admin)
  - Account list with quick metrics and action menu (view details, suspend, change plan)
  - User list with roles and SSO indicators; inline role change dropdown
  - Support tickets list with filters and assignment

Accessibility:
- All charts should include aria labels and a text-mode summary export for screen readers
- Ensure color contrast meets WCAG AA for text and critical indicators
- Keyboard navigable and forms with proper labels

### Backend
- Implement REST (or GraphQL) endpoints:
  - GET /api/projects/:projectId/analytics?start=&end=&groupBy=&filters=...
  - GET /api/accounts/:accountId/analytics?...
  - GET /api/analytics/decisions?filters=&page=&limit=&sort=
  - POST /api/exports (body includes scope, filters, format) -> returns exportId
  - GET /api/exports/:exportId/status and GET /api/exports/:exportId/download
  - CRUD /api/alerts
  - Admin endpoints: GET /api/admin/usage, GET /api/admin/accounts, POST /api/admin/accounts/:id/action, GET /api/admin/auditlogs
  - Support tickets endpoints: GET/POST/PUT /api/support/tickets
- Database tables (suggested):
  - decisions (existing) — ensure fields: id, project_id, account_id, created_at, decision_made_at, status, reviewer_id, type, tags
  - decision_events (existing) — timestamps for state transitions and comments
  - analytics_aggregates (new) — daily aggregates per project/account with fields: date, project_id, account_id, decisions_count, median_approval_seconds, pct_within_sla, avg_response_seconds, pending_count
  - alerts (new) — id, name, scope_type, scope_id, metric, operator, threshold_value, frequency, channels (json), enabled, last_triggered_at, created_by
  - exports (new) — id, requested_by, scope, filters_json, format, status, s3_path, rows_count, created_at, completed_at
  - audit_logs (new) — id, actor_id, actor_role, action_type, target_type, target_id, details_json, created_at
  - support_tickets (new) — id, account_id, created_by, assigned_to, priority, status, subject, body, comments_json, created_at, updated_at
- Aggregation jobs:
  - Real-time triggers (on decision_made event) to update short-term aggregates
  - Nightly job to compute materialized aggregates for date ranges, percentiles
  - Use time-series friendly storage or rollups for performance
- Export pipeline:
  - Exports are queued, processed by worker generating CSV in streaming fashion, stored to object storage (S3), and signed URL provided to frontend.
- Alert evaluation:
  - Scheduled worker runs to evaluate alerts; on trigger, push notifications via configured channels and log to alert history
- Security:
  - Enforce RBAC at API layer: project-level users can only query project analytics; account admins can query account rollups; platform admins have cross-account access.
  - For admin APIs require MFA and admin role check
- Telemetry:
  - Log usage of analytics pages, export requests, and alert triggers for auditing and product analytics

### Integration
- Data flow:
  - Source data: decisions and decision_events (existing system)
  - Aggregator: worker updates analytics_aggregates table in near-real-time and computes percentiles for median approval time
  - API layer queries either precomputed aggregates or, for ad-hoc ranges, runs efficient aggregation queries with indexes
  - Export API requests queued to export worker which reads decisions/aggregates, streams CSV to S3, updates exports table
  - Alerts engine reads aggregates and/or raw events; triggers when condition met, calling notification service (email, webhook)
  - Admin pages call admin APIs that query aggregates, audit logs, and support tickets
- Frontend connects to API endpoints; uses WebSocket or server-sent events for long-running export progress and real-time alert notifications

## User Experience Flow
1. User (project manager) navigates to Project > Analytics & Reports.
2. Default view shows last 30 days KPIs and a Bottleneck Heatmap for that project.
3. User adjusts filters: sets date range to last 90 days, filters to "Finishes" decision type, and toggles SLA overlay.
4. KPI cards update; user clicks the median approval time card to drill into histogram.
5. In histogram, they select the highest bucket; the Slow Decisions Table filters to show those decisions.
6. User selects several decisions and clicks "Export Selected" — ReportBuilderModal opens pre-populated with the selection and export format CSV.
7. User starts export; modal shows export queued. ExportHistory shows progress; when complete user downloads CSV.
8. User creates an alert: name "Slow Finishes", scope project, metric median approval time > 72 hours, notifications via email + webhook. Alert is recorded and scheduled for evaluation.
9. Admin (platform) visits /admin and sees account-level usage: top accounts by decisions/month, system health (worker queue depth high), and open support tickets. Admin assigns a ticket to on-call and suspends a problematic account if needed.

